    • Method Detail

      • fireMessage

        void fireMessage(IFIXMessage message)
          throws Exception
        Passes on the given FIX message to be ultimately sent over a FIX session.

        The actual FIX session that the message will be sent over depends on the way the listeners to this message processor registered themselves.

        See fireMessage(IConnectionPoint, IFIXMessage) for firing a message to a specific FIX session.

        Parameters:
        message - Message to be sent over FIX.
        Throws:
        Exception - If there is a problem sending the message over FIX.

      • fireMessage

        void fireMessage(IConnectionPoint cp,
                 IFIXMessage message)
          throws Exception,
                 RoutingException
        Passes on the given FIX message to be ultimately sent over the FIX session associated with the given connection point.

        This is directed routing in contrast to the fireMessage(IFIXMessage) method where the routing is controlled by the way the listeners registered themselves.

        Parameters:
        cp - Connection point.
        message - Message to be sent over FIX.
        Throws:
        Exception - If there is a problem sending the message over FIX.
        RoutingException - if there is no listener associated with the given connection point.

      • getConnectionPoints

        Set<IConnectionPoint> getConnectionPoints()
        Returns all IConnectionPoints associated with listeners to source messages fired by this message processor.
        Returns:
        Set of IConnectionPoint objects.

      • onMessageToFix

        void onMessageToFix(MessageEvent event,
                    IFIXMessage message)
             throws Exception
        This will be called if your processor is in a chain of processors. The message has been passed on to you by a previous IFIXSource processor. You should process the given message.

        By default the message event is then automatically forwarded on to the next processor in the chain unless you have thrown exception indicating that you were unable to process the message.

        If you want to take over the responsibility for forwarding messages on, you should call setAutoForwarding(false).

        Parameters:
        event - the message event
        message - the message
        Throws:
        Exception - if an exception occurs when processing the message
